habitat_comment: Tolerant of vegetation but possibly high collision risk due to habitat use.
"Prefers open water without emergent or dense submerged vegetation."
"Feeds in open water; usually avoids dense aquatic vegetation which is rare in its breeding areas."
Tricky one, hang out on shorelines but not as important for habitat as for other species.

"Presently breeds primarily in lowland areas along ocean coasts, rivers, streams, lakes, reservoirs, and wetlands (Cramp 1988, Turner and Rose 1989a, Am. Ornithol. Union American Ornithologists' Union 1998a). "
